    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A synthetic, permanent, stable white pigment prepared from precipitated barium sulfate (barite) since ca.1820s. The pure white powder is transparent when used as a filler or base for lake pigments. The reproducible whiteness of high purity led to its use in the standard white tiles for reflectance spectrophotometry. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
